## Source comment consistency evidence

`nl -ba modules/gemini-bloom/src/sb_chain.h | sed -n '84,96p'` returned:

```text
    88	// Wire-format structures for BF.SCANDUMP / BF.LOADCHUNK.
    89	// Field order, types, and packing match the RedisBloom binary protocol
    90	// for cross-implementation compatibility. Verified against RedisBloom
    91	// v2.4.20 (Redis 6.2.17).
```

This conflicts with DESIGN.md lines 166, 484, and 528-536, which define SCANDUMP/LOADCHUNK as a private non-interoperable protocol.
